abstract: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
snippet: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Maybe it was the threat of bad weather. Maybe it was a seating assignment debacle. Maybe it was a struggling campaign organization that still hadn’t found its footing.

headline_main: State of the Union Address, Impeachment, Iowa: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
snippet: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
lead_paragraph: On Monday night, the Iowa caucuses ended in chaos. More important, the partial results released on Tuesday suggest that the Democratic path to the White House remains rocky.

headline_main: If Bernie Wins, Where Will He Take the Democratic Party?

abstract: Buttigieg and Sanders were triumphant. But Trump had a few things he wanted to say for himself.
snippet: Buttigieg and Sanders were triumphant. But Trump had a few things he wanted to say for himself.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Just when I thought the Iowa caucus, and maybe the Democratic nomination, was in the bag for Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg pulled out what looks to be either a largely unpredicted first-place finish in the Hawkeye State or at least a close second-place.
